coupled_prompt_600: Gabriel Mato Adrover is a politician and writer based in Madrid, Spain. He was elected as the regionalist leader of the Popular Party (PP) from the town of Cádiz in 2014. He previously served as deputy president of the PP and as mayor of Ciudad Real. He now serves as vice chairman of the Spanish Confederation of Industries (ECI). In his free time he enjoys reading and writing in both Spanish and English. He's working on the second volume of his memoirs called The End of the Story: My Life Among the Extremists. A photo of Gabriel has been taken by Maria José Luis at La Voz de Galicia in Spain, April 2015.
